  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>Primary wound closure</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Experimental</arm_group_type>
    <description>A wound will be sutured immediately after the operative procedure uisng non-absorbable monofilament suture or stapler at intervals of one centimeter apart and 0.5 cm back from a wound edge.</description>
  </arm_group>
  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>Delayed primary wound closure</arm_group_label>
    <arm_group_type>Active Comparator</arm_group_type>
    <description>A wound will be left open with saline-soaked gauze packing after the operative procedure and will be sutured around day 3 to 7 after operation</description>
  </arm_group>
